arts.ttl: Charlie Kelman hails Leyton Orient's FA Cup progress
arts.sum: They were frightening at times, but we knew that if we stuck with it and got the early goal - we conceded after that - in the past we could have turned over, but we always felt like we were in control of the game and that we were going to win it in the end.” On his goal, Kelman gave a vague account of the sequence of events that preceded the opportunity to open the scoring after just 20 minutes.
